stayed at Shar-e-naw hotel Bed and Breakfast a few years ago and it was a very positive experience in all respects. Since then the owner has expanded and opened a small hotel a block away from the guesthouse. Both the guesthouse and the hotel offer first class amenities and comforts. But what makes both of these places stand out is the warm and generous hospitality that makes you feel like a cherished guest. Free pick up and drop off at the airport is welcome as flights from Europe tend to arrive and leave at ungodly hours. The free breakfast is generous and good. The staff also go out of their way to solve any problems you may have (In my case a lost luggage). The location is abour 30 minute from airport the best place in kabul and the city centre. It is about 20 minutes walk to the city centre, but the hotel can help with transport at little cost. They can also arrange hiring a cart with driver at a very reasonable price. The lack of a in-house restaurant is made up for by an arrangement for free delivery service from 4-5 good restaurants. After ordering a dinner it took 25-30 minutes to arrive, . All in all Shar-e-naw hotel truly lives up to the aspiration of offering a home away from home   (OSM data version: 2016-06-01T10:03:02Z) #mapsme
